	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Atlanta Geo</placeName> <date>Aug 27th 67</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee> <del>Esqr</del></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philada&#44; Pa.</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Revd &#38; Dear Sir.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your esteemed<lb/>favor of the <date>23rd</date> inst came to hand<lb/> this day&#44; <del>upon</del> the eve of my de<lb/>parture for <placeName>New York</placeName>. I am<lb/> consequently unable to give my<lb/> personal attention to your<lb/> commission but have left<lb/> its execution in the hands of<lb/> my brother&#44; <persName>Julius</persName>&#44; who will<lb/> see your instructions carried<lb/> out to the letter. The box directed<lb/> to me has not yet arrived but<lb/> as soon as it does the matter<lb/> will be attended to &#38;  you will<lb/> receive the money promptly.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You are mistaken when<lb/> you suppose that there are not</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>many of our people who en<lb/>quire after you. On the con<lb/>trary there is scarcely a meeting<lb/> takes place among us for the<lb/> discussion of topics connected<lb/> with the welfare of the Jewish<lb/> people but your name is<lb/> mentioned with especial <hi rend="underline">love</hi>.<lb/> I honestly believe there is no<lb/> man in <placeName>America</placeName> who possesses<lb/> more universally the love &#38;<lb/> esteem of both friends &#38; foes<lb/> than you do and no one<lb/> but gives you praise you have<lb/> merited by a life well spent<lb/> in doing good.  And all unite<lb/> in the prayers that the Lord may<lb/> spare your life for many days<lb/> for the sake of the good works you<lb/> have done in his Holy name.<lb/>  Your friend <persName>Dr Brantly<add>&#63;</add></persName> has<lb/> inquired after you several times<lb/> and always seems gratified</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>to learn of you.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Please send to <persName>S. Meyers</persName><lb/> <placeName>Columbus Geo</placeName></p>
				<p>1 Copy of the &#8220;Occident&#8221; for the ensuing year</p>
				<p>1 Almanac latest edition</p>
				<p>1 Daily Prayer book in Hebrew<lb/> and English neatly bound&#44; 8 <add>&#63;</add>.<lb/> with the <del>initials</del> name &#8220;<persName>R. B. Meyer</persName>&#8221;<lb/> embossed in gilt letters upon<lb/> the cover.  Send the books by<lb/> express to <persName>Mr. M.</persName> at <placeName>Columbus</placeName><lb/> <hi rend="underline">with the bill</hi> so that he can<lb/> send you the amount.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">With my best regards<lb/> in which all the family join</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am yours very Truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">J. C. Alexander</persName></p>
				<p>I must beg you to excuse the many<lb/> erasures in the foregoing as I am in<lb/> such a hurry preparing to leave<lb/> that I have scarcely time to con<lb/>centrate my thoughts upon any one</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>thing &#38; hence many expressions<lb/> &#38; words crept in which were<lb/> afterwards discarded for these<lb/> which better expressed my<lb/> meaning.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr &#38; Mrs Meyers</persName> request<lb/> me to return thanks for your<lb/> kind wishes.</p>
		</body>
